what do you think about severus snape after reading harry potter and the deathly hallows severus snape definitely the flawed hero a hero but nevertheless a jerk i guess he can be forgiven for that though i love the way he says look at me to harry before he dies like he wanted to die looking into those eyes lily's eyes he clearly loved lily all his life this love is what led him to work against the dark side being the jerk he is i dont see snape going against voldemort if voldemort had not killed lily that night at godric's hallow after being portrayed as this cold and impassive man for six books to see him in this new light has given me new found respect for this man for he was brave and honorable even though it was for his own selfish reasons he made wrong choices but did redeem himself in the end his character has multiple layers and thats what makes him so interesting and his redemptive pattern is remarkable James and Lily Potter Severus Snape Harry Potter (character) Lord Voldemort Harry Potter: Book Seven Horace Slughorn Dates in Harry Potter Hogwarts subjects Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix Remus Lupin Albus Dumbledore Order of the Phoenix Hogwarts Houses Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban (film) Sybill Trelawney Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince Professor Quirrell Death Eater Half-Blood Prince (character) Minor Dark wizards in Harry Potter Blood purity (Harry Potter) Battle of Hogwarts Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire Magic (Harry Potter) Ginny Weasley Magical objects in Harry Potter Harry Potter Ron Weasley Hermione Granger Hogwarts Bellatrix Lestrange Alan Rickman Peter Pettigrew Messiahs in fiction and fantasy Legilimency Minor members of the Order of the Phoenix Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone (video game) Dark Mark Rubeus Hagrid Neville Longbottom Narcissa Malfoy Fan fiction Harry Potter and the Chamber of Secrets Occlumency Dark Art Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone (film) 